HEADWORD: Heelpiece
<hw>Heel"piece`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
piece of armor to protect the heels.</def>
<rj><au>Chesterfield.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A piece of leather fixed on the heel of a
shoe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The end.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>heelpiece</xex> of
his book.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Lloyd.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heelpost</ent>⟦br⟧
